01:25:36.795 --> 01:25:39.590 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our postcard for this month is from Albania,

01:25:39.590 --> 01:25:42.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
a small country on the Adriatic Sea.

01:25:43.093 --> 01:25:45.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
For much of its tumultuous past,

01:25:45.095 --> 01:25:48.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
foreign powers have come and gone,

01:25:48.140 --> 01:25:50.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
each bringing with it
a different mix of peoples,

01:25:50.434 --> 01:25:53.145 line:90% position:50% align:center
cultures, and religions.

01:25:53.145 --> 01:25:57.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
Albania is a beautiful land,
scattered with lakes

01:25:57.274 --> 01:25:59.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
and crisscrossed by rivers.

01:25:59.944 --> 01:26:02.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
Idyllic beaches dot the coastline,

01:26:02.071 --> 01:26:05.032 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as the aptly named Aquarium Beach,

01:26:05.032 --> 01:26:07.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
a beautiful spot for snorkeling.

01:26:08.286 --> 01:26:11.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Karavasta Lagoon,
the largest in the country,

01:26:11.706 --> 01:26:14.292 line:90% position:50% align:center
is the home
of the Dalmatian pelican,

01:26:14.292 --> 01:26:16.294 line:90% position:50% align:center
the largest of its kind,

01:26:16.294 --> 01:26:19.172 line:90% position:50% align:center
measuring up to 1.8 meters (6 ft) long.

01:26:20.631 --> 01:26:24.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
In Romans chapter 15,
the apostle Paul reported

01:26:24.260 --> 01:26:28.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
that he and his companions
had “thoroughly preached the good news.”

01:26:28.514 --> 01:26:31.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
They had traveled “as far as Illyricum,”

01:26:31.100 --> 01:26:34.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
a Roman province
that included part of what is today Albania.

01:26:35.647 --> 01:26:39.817 line:90% position:50% align:center
It is likely that some in the region
became Christians at that time,

01:26:39.817 --> 01:26:42.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
for secular history reports that Christianity

01:26:42.570 --> 01:26:44.572 line:90% position:50% align:center
took root in Albania in the first century.

01:26:45.240 --> 01:26:47.242 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the 1920’s,

01:26:47.242 --> 01:26:49.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
some Albanians learned Bible truth

01:26:49.327 --> 01:26:51.913 line:90% position:50% align:center
while living in the United States.

01:26:51.913 --> 01:26:55.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
After getting baptized,
some returned to Albania,

01:26:55.083 --> 01:26:57.168 line:90% position:50% align:center
eager to share these precious truths

01:26:57.168 --> 01:26:59.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
with family and friends.

01:26:59.671 --> 01:27:03.758 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1928,
Lazar Nasson and Petro Stavro

01:27:03.758 --> 01:27:06.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
traveled from the United States
back to Albania

01:27:06.720 --> 01:27:09.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
to show the “Photo-Drama of Creation.”

01:27:09.514 --> 01:27:11.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many responded,

01:27:11.141 --> 01:27:14.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
and despite political turmoil,
economic reversal

01:27:14.561 --> 01:27:17.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
and, at times, vigorous opposition,

01:27:17.022 --> 01:27:21.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
the number of Kingdom proclaimers
has grown steadily.

01:27:21.151 --> 01:27:25.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, there are more than 5,400 publishers

01:27:25.739 --> 01:27:28.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
serving in 89 congregations.

01:27:28.617 --> 01:27:30.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
From Tirana, the capital,

01:27:30.827 --> 01:27:33.330 line:90% position:50% align:center
the branch office
cares for the work in Albania

01:27:33.330 --> 01:27:38.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the 228 publishers
in its northeast neighbor, Kosovo.

01:27:39.169 --> 01:27:43.799 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s visit the city of Lushnjë,
located in west-central Albania.

01:27:45.217 --> 01:27:48.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Lushnjë Veriu Congregation
preaches in a territory

01:27:48.011 --> 01:27:50.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
that covers around one third of the city

01:27:50.806 --> 01:27:54.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
as well as 21 villages in the Myzeqe Valley.

01:27:54.643 --> 01:27:58.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
The preaching work in the villages
yields good results,

01:27:58.731 --> 01:28:03.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
and meeting attendance
regularly averages over 130 percent.

01:28:03.402 --> 01:28:07.156 line:90% position:50% align:center
They are happy to host 
a Romany-language group.

01:28:07.156 --> 01:28:10.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
Though some publishers
live in villages outside the city,

01:28:10.409 --> 01:28:13.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
they are happy
to attend the meetings in person,

01:28:13.787 --> 01:28:17.625 line:90% position:50% align:center
some walking one hour
from their home to the Kingdom Hall.

01:28:18.459 --> 01:28:22.296 line:90% position:50% align:center
The 77 publishers
of the Lushnjë Veriu Congregation

01:28:22.296 --> 01:28:25.800 line:90% position:50% align:center
send you
their Christian affection and greetings!

01:28:26.425 --> 01:28:29.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:28:29.553 --> 01:28:32.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

